<Author>bufffan08
<Content>Don't do it! We booked this hotel on the recommendation of relatives that live in Puerto Rico. (I'm thinking they picked it just because, not because they'd had any dealings with the hotel) Anyway, the hotel has a lot of charm and is clean (except for the carpet) with a friendly and helpful staff, but that's as much praise as I'll give it. Our room was SMALL and musty smelling. There were those little tiny black ants in the bathroom. The knob on the bathroom sink came off with a lift. The shower handle was a challenge. There wasn't much play to the handle. The first night my husband ended up taking a cold shower because he hadn't figured out the trick to get the handle to turn in order to have hot water. The two other groups of family members staying at the hotel didn't get a shower the first night, because the hotels power went off/surged for a moment, thus rendering the hotel waterless for a couple of hours, apparently a common accurance. Thin pillows like the other review said. Also, amazed that there are no hand towels and only one wash cloth besides the two bath towels and bath mat. The street noise, people walking by talking, etc. are very noticable, as if the window were open when it wasn't. And to finish, we were there for four nights, and on the last night, I discovered the carpet is in desperate need of a shampooing. I put on a pair of socks after a day on the beach and had them on maybe, ten minutes, and had made a few trips around the room, back and forth to the bathroom, etc. then sat down on the bed and caught a look at the bottom of my feet--my white socks were black, YUCK! I'm glad that I hadn't noticed this on the first day, 'cause that would of made the stay that much worse, knowing what I was walking on and going to be walking on for the rest of my vacation. Similar complaints from our other family members staying at the hotel. I'd never stay there again...charm is wonderful, but so are a ton of other things. 
