<Author>travelers56
<Content>I do not understand the good reviews. Horrible room, uncaring staff, very rude owner. It looked so quant from the photos but the room was an absolute dump and I have stayed in quite a few Motel 6 and similar. The very small room with a great view of the parking lot and trash bins (that were noisily utilized all night) had an uncomfortable old mattress with no mattress pad and no blanket (you use the bed cover I guess). The sheets were so thin I could easily see the mattress print. Towels were thin with rips and holes and the towel rack was hanging from the wall. There was a 1/2 inch gap to the outside around the noisy air conditioner and the shower temperature control was broken. (They stated they wanted to send in an outside handyman into my room to fix the shower and wanted to know if it was okay. Since when does a hotel not take responsibility for who they send in?) The mirror was a medicine cabinet that was not under the light and would not stay closed because the magnet was missing. I had to shave with one had on the mirror holding it closed. The CAT5 phone line was just punched though the wall with a two inch hole and then ran down the outside of the wall. The walls were cracked and paint lifted from mold or water damage or who knows what. I kept expecting a [--] come through the door any minute.Also all the basics you take for granted were missing such as hangers, an iron, a pen and pad, a hook on the back side of the door for your toiletry bag, etc... I guess what was irritating was that 90% of the problems could have been fixed with $50 and an hour of their time.Also note that they require a copy of your driver鈥檚 license and credit card and do not destroy it or give it back when you leave. They keep it on file forever they said. What?!?!?I gave up after one night and headed across the street to Embassy Suites. For $50 more and I got a very nice suite with a TV/wet bar sitting area and separate nice bedroom overlooking the pool. It even included free breakfasts. And best of all it was run like a real hotel by nice caring staff. However, it was even closer to the airport and noisy out by the pool during plane take off. All other decent hotels were at least double the cost though.I usually prefer small BB and private hotels but this one was a major disappointment to put it mildly. Some friends arrived the next day and also had horror stories and left after one night. They were so glad to get out. I鈥檇 avoid it at all costs. 
