<Content>small, but clean and affordable We just needed a place to stay for the night before we flew out. I prefer staying at smaller quaint places with personality, rather than hotel chains. Going by trip advisor recommendations, I thought I'd give this place a shot. I couldn't believe the price! San Juan prices were all high, and at $90 a night, I was a little nervous about what I was getting in to. But it wasn't bad! Pros are the bar, the pool, the patio upstairs, the cleanliness. The staff was nice, and it was close to the beach. There's a cafe on the corner across the street to get coffee in the morning.Cons: It was difficult getting the luggage up the stairs. Whatever they use to clean the bathrooms smelled way too strong, almost nauseating, so we bought some incense and it made the smell go away. No coffee in the rooms or in the lobby. The air conditioner was a little loud, but it turned out good for drowning out the sounds of the airport. If you don't plan to spend too much time in the room it was sufficient just to sleep. The bathroom was small, but the shower had pretty good pressure and water was hot. All in all, I would stay there again, but I would check out the bigger more expensive rooms if I needed more than one night. 
